snippet: A 16-year-old girl who survived a small-plane crash in the thickly forested mountains of north-central Washington State emerged from the wilderness after hiking for a couple of days.
abstract: Teenager Autumn Veatch emerges from woods two days after small plane crashes in mountains of north-central Washington State; authorities are searching for other passengers, including her two step-grandparents.
lead_paragraph: A 16-year-old girl who survived a small-plane crash in the thickly forested mountains of north-central Washington State emerged from the wilderness after hiking for a couple of days.

headline.main: Washington: Girl Walks Out of Woods 2 Days After Disappearance of Plane
headline.print_headline: Washington: Girl Walks Out of Woods 2 Days After Disappearance of Plane
